.TH "genwqe_crc16" 9 "genwqe_crc16" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
genwqe_crc16 \- Generate 16-bit crc as required for DDCBs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u16" genwqe_crc16
.BI "(const u8 *buff "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "u16 init "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buff" 12
pointer to data buffer
.IP "len" 12
length of data for calculation
.IP "init" 12
initial crc (0xffff at start)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Polynomial = x^16 + x^12 + x^5 + 1   (0x1021)
.SH "EXAMPLE"
4 bytes 0x01 0x02 0x03 0x04 with init = 0xffff
should result in a crc16 of 0x89c3
.SH "RETURN"
crc16 checksum in big endian format !
